Description: Sherd from foot of East Greek, possibly Chian small pottery vessel; the upper surface has the appearance of being fenestrated; creamy slip; interior reserved; exterior: rays between thin bands; slight traces of glaze above, coinciding with the remains of additional features on the upper surface; inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: For parallels, see British Museum 1888,0601.187. The slip found on sections of the 'break' indicate that the sherd does not belong to a rim.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GD.2203)
